				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Tanadil wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Hey guys try to kill Buch as much as possible so he feels at home, altho from friends who play WoW Rangers are supposed to be a really great character class to play!!!  GO RANGER POWA!!!  Just seeing you around here Buch and nynji and Goth!  TAKE IT EASY MAN!</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
It's funny, Tan... WoW doesn't really have "rangers" - the closest thing would be a Hunter.  But Hunters are really like a mix of Rangers and Beastlords.  They get the Archery like a Ranger, but they have Pets like a Beastlord.  And the sweet thing is they can have any beast in the game (not Humanoids) for a pet - you just walk up to one and charm it and BAM - it's your pet till you get rid of it.  The charm never wears off.  And your pet will level up with you and gain EXP while you do.
<br />

<br />
A lot of people have this opinion that Hunters are a really powerful class - I agree they are a great class... but they are a little tough to play at first.  They don't have any heals, and they have very few buffs at first so they are kinda tough to fight with.  You don't get your first real pet until 10th level so before then it's all solo.  I could see where at higher levels Hunters might be really nasty... but getting there has got to be rough.
<br />

<br />
Of course Nynji could fill you in on Hunters more!  He and his pet crab, Sancho, are totally Ub3r!!!  Sancho tanks better than me - and I'm a Pally!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: yellow">HEY GOTHRA</span></span> - where are you, man?  Did you get your game?  Have you made a character on Alleria yet?  Why not!?!
<br />
<span style="color: black">...
<br />
Subliminal Message... ES people need to try WoW... ES people need to try WoW... =)
<br />
...</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
